[{"id":41384,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["one","four","two","three"],"answer":3,"solution":"Change in momentum for each bullet fired is\n$$\n=\\frac{40}{1000} \\times 1200=48 \\mathrm{~N}\n$$\nIf a bullet fired exerts a force of $48 \\mathrm{~N}$ on man's hand so $\\rho$ man can exert maximum force of $144 \\mathrm{~N}$, number of bullets that can be fired $=144 / 48=3$ bullets.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":41266,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9c6cd1c7-71d1-4e72-81b9-8201484cb44b-image.png\" style=\"width: 140px; height: 140px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/578dc3b3-0d4d-4af9-ac2d-dff447b1d31e-image.png\" style=\"width: 140px; height: 145px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c9683de6-a6d9-4f50-8e99-408a10745ce1-image.png\" style=\"width: 140px; height: 142px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9b999322-5431-431f-b592-79cbd1473201-image.png\" style=\"width: 140px; height: 136px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The required centripetal force will be provided by the normal reaction</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>This equation is similar to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;which is a parabola.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41301,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Impulse <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math> change in momentum</p><p>Ball (a) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>|</mo><mover><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>|</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>J</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></p><p>Ball (b) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>|</mo><mover><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>|</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>cos</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>J</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>J</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>J</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41397,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["8 : 1","9 : 7","4 : 3","5 : 3"],"answer":1,"solution":"$a=\\frac{m_1-m_2}{m_1+m_2} g ; \\frac{1}{8}=\\frac{m_1-m_2}{m_1+m_2} \\Rightarrow m_1: m_2=9: 7$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":41286,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c1d42c44-ab25-463d-97d3-5c3401474c19-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 160px;\" /></p><p>Acceleration,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Net</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>pulling</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>force</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>Total</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mass</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>g</mi></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Considering ball&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>10</mn></math> as system, tension between ball 7 &amp; 8 can be written as,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>a</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41386,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$2.0$","$4.0$","$1.6$","$2.5$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{m}=2 \\mathrm{~kg}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":41262,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/804bd665-df71-4134-bb57-9a5ece22d193-43fe43ae-e219-4bf7-84af-3953c7ce449d-9893439.PNG\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 158px;\" /></p><p>The magnitude of acceleration of both the blocks will be same and is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mn>60</mn><mo>&#8728;</mo></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mn>30</mn><mo>&#8728;</mo></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Applying Newton&#39;s second law for second block (along the direction parallel to the incline on which it is placed)</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>a</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (24 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41230,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Net force <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p>Therefore, required acceleration <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>a</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi>i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41226,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"FBD of $M_1$ :\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/N05qK9mwA7KGvi1eCO3kxzUa-5_iBViHJt3sVZFBc9I.original.fullsize.png\"><br />$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{T}_1-200=(4+6+10) \\times 2 \\\\\n& \\therefore \\mathrm{T}_1=240\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41398,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["9.2","7.8","4","9.8"],"answer":1,"solution":"Apply Newton's second law\n$$\n\\mathrm{F}-\\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{ab}}=m a ; \\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{ab}}-\\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{bc}}=\\mathrm{ma} \\quad \\therefore \\mathrm{T}_{\\mathrm{bc}}=7.8 \\mathrm{~N}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":41250,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>33</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>35</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>N</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>The free body diagram for the given scenario is shown below-</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c9011b60-eb82-4711-b999-e2db146ea818-9896627_2.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 317px;\" /></p><p>From the equilibrium of the vertical component of forces, it can be written that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>N</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>100</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>200</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>F</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>From the equilibrium of horizontal component of forces, it can be written that,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>N</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>Substitute the expression for the normal reaction force from equation (1) into equation (2) and solve to calculate the value of the applied force.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>200</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>F</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>F</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>200</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>F</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>F</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>200</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8776;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (01 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41322,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b6177da9-dc04-4039-9fa8-cf99056d6ae0-image.png\" style=\"width: 272px; height: 220px;\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>mgsin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>mgcos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>37</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mn>37</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41255,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["c and a","b and c","c and b","a and b"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/05eaffdb-8170-4080-bb0e-26c6664da388-9895372.PNG\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 241px;\" /></p><p>From Newton&#39;s second,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mi>F</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mi>slope</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>curve</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>From the given graph, we can see that slope of region&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;is maximum and slope of region&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;is minimum.</p><p>Thus,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>c</mi></msub></mfenced><mo>&#62;</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>a</mi></msub></mfenced><mo>&#62;</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>b</mi></msub></mfenced></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41203,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["25","7.5","12.5","15"],"answer":2,"solution":"For motion without acceleration, net force = 0.<br>Component of weight along incline: $mg\\sin(30°) = 5 \\times 10 \\times 0.5 = 25$ N (down).<br>Normal force: $N = mg\\cos(30°) = 50 \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} = 25\\sqrt{3}$ N.<br>Friction force opposing downward motion:<br>$f = \\mu N = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\times 25\\sqrt{3} = 37.5$ N (up).<br>For equilibrium along the incline, applying force F down the incline:<br>$mg\\sin\\theta + F = f$, so $25 + F = 37.5$, giving $F = 12.5$ N.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41337,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi> </mi><msup><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mn>0</mn></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/spdbzrbxamgsfyqjrebgqhrzkmoncqdxmxpcqkdedpfdvjsefq.png\" /><br /><math><mi>N</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>a</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><math> <mrow> <msup> <mi>t</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41333,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">γ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ln</mi></mrow><mo>⁡</mo><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">γ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">γ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">tan</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>⁡</mo><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">γ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">γ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>⁡</mo><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">γ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>γ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">tan</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>⁡</mo><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>γ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Net force on ball,<br /><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><mrow><munderover><mo stretchy=\"true\">&#8747;</mo><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munderover><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></mrow></mrow><mrow><munderover><mo stretchy=\"true\">&#8747;</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></munderover><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mrow></math><br /><math><msubsup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></msqrt></mfrac><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41385,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$0.2 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$9.8 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$5 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$4.8 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{a}=\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{m}_1-\\mathrm{m}_2}{\\mathrm{~m}_1+\\mathrm{m}_2}\\right) \\mathrm{g}=0.2 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":41225,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$196 \\mathrm{~N}$","$291 \\mathrm{~N}$","$294 \\mathrm{~N}$","$297 \\mathrm{~N}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Taking $\\mathrm{g}=9.8 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ScCIp3P53LCTDhpSRZi9mHsd3VT58LqoaUOVwexEetk.original.fullsize.png\"><br />$\\begin{aligned} & 294-\\mathrm{N}=30 \\times 0.1 \\\\ & \\mathrm{~N}=291\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41390,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$0.02$","$0.03$","$0.04$","None of  these"],"answer":3,"solution":"$a=\\mu g=\\frac{6}{10}$             [ using $\\mathrm{v}=\\mathrm{u}+\\mathrm{at}$ ]\n$\\Rightarrow \\mu=\\frac{6}{10 \\times g}=\\frac{6}{10 \\times 10}=0.06$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":41323,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>b</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>dM</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>dt</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>bv</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br />in free space no external force so there in only thrust force on rocket<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><msub><mi>V</mi><mrow><mi>r</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></msub></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mi>v</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>bv</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41284,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>39</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>49</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>78</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Maximum acceleration of the upper block will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Therefore, maximum force that can be applied on the lower block is,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>49</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41304,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>t</mi><mi>d</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>a</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8230;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">d</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi></math></p><p>Using the above values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>a</mi></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></msub></math> and putting in<br />equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math>, we will get,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41361,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$9.8 \\mathrm{~m}$","$27 \\mathrm{~m}$","$12 \\mathrm{~m}$","$3.33 \\mathrm{~m}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"When the body has maximum speed then\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mu=0.3 \\mathrm{x}=\\tan 45^{\\circ} \\\\\n& \\therefore \\mathrm{x}=3.33 \\mathrm{~m}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (22 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41199,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$3/4$","$2/3$","$5/9$","$4/9$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Let the length of the inclined plane be $s$.<br><br>For the smooth inclined plane, the acceleration of the block is $a_1 = g \\sin \\theta$.<br><br>The time taken to slide down is $t_1 = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2s}{a_1}} = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2s}{g \\sin \\theta}}$.<br><br>For the rough inclined plane, the acceleration of the block is $a_2 = g \\sin \\theta - \\mu_k g \\cos \\theta$.<br><br>The time taken to slide down is $t_2 = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2s}{a_2}} = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2s}{g (\\sin \\theta - \\mu_k \\cos \\theta)}}$.<br><br>Given that $t_2$ is $50\\%$ more than $t_1$, we have $t_2 = t_1 + 0.5 t_1 = \\dfrac{3}{2} t_1$.<br><br>Squaring both sides gives $t_2^2 = \\dfrac{9}{4} t_1^2$.<br><br>Substituting the expressions for $t_1^2$ and $t_2^2$:<br><br>$\\dfrac{2s}{g (\\sin \\theta - \\mu_k \\cos \\theta)} = \\dfrac{9}{4} \\left( \\dfrac{2s}{g \\sin \\theta} \\right)$<br><br>$\\dfrac{1}{\\sin \\theta - \\mu_k \\cos \\theta} = \\dfrac{9}{4 \\sin \\theta}$<br><br>$4 \\sin \\theta = 9 \\sin \\theta - 9 \\mu_k \\cos \\theta$<br><br>$9 \\mu_k \\cos \\theta = 5 \\sin \\theta$<br><br>$\\mu_k = \\dfrac{5}{9} \\tan \\theta$<br><br>Given $\\theta = 45^\\circ$, we have $\\tan 45^\\circ = 1$.<br><br>$\\mu_k = \\dfrac{5}{9} \\times 1 = \\dfrac{5}{9}$<br><br>Answer: $5/9$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (04 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41268,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>18</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given that the mass of the air&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>&nbsp;and it escapes in time&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;with velocity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p><p>The average force on the balloon can be given as,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>dyne</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41344,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Time taken to slide along a smooth surface is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>.<br /><math><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>g</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><msup><mrow><mn>45</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>o</mi></mrow></msup><msubsup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mrow></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>s</mi></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br />Time taken to slide along a rough surface&nbsp;is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>g</mi><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#8289;</mo><msup><mn>45</mn><mi>o</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#8289;</mo><msup><mn>45</mn><mi>o</mi></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi>&#160;</mi><msubsup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>s</mi></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>&#956;</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>s</mi></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>&#956;</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>s</mi></msqrt></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null},{"id":41217,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["39 N","15 N","11 N","20 N"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{kx}_1=5 \\mathrm{~N} \\\\ & \\mathrm{kx}_2=7 \\mathrm{~N} \\\\ & \\mathrm{k}\\left(5 \\mathrm{x}_1-2 \\mathrm{x}_2\\right)=5 \\mathrm{kx}_1-2 \\mathrm{kx}_2 \\\\ & =5 \\times 5-2 \\times 7=11 \\mathrm{~N}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41295,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given</p><p>Translation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi></math> of electron</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>e</mi><mi>V</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>38</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>23</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>19</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>773</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>773</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>273</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>500</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41326,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>l</mi><msup><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>l</mi><msup><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>l</mi><msup><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>l</mi><msup><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>ω</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0cc9ff3d-4a0c-4578-89ae-386c6fe6e5e0-image.png\" /></p><p>As we know, the spring force will give the necessary centripetal force for rotation.</p><p>So,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>l</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>l</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>&nbsp;Thus, the stretch in the spring<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>l</mi><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41341,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$1.00 \\mathrm{~cm}$","$0.25 \\mathrm{~cm}$","$0.37 \\mathrm{~cm}$","$0.75 \\mathrm{~cm}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"For same material the ratio of stress to strain is same For first cube\n$$\n\\text { Stress }_1=\\frac{\\text { force }_1}{\\text { area }_1}=\\frac{10^5}{\\left(0.1^2\\right)}\n$$\nFor second block,\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\text { stress }_2=\\frac{\\text { force }_2}{\\text { area }_2}=\\frac{10^5}{\\left(0.2^2\\right)} \\\\\n&\\text { strain }_2=\\frac{\\text { change in length }{ }_2}{\\text { original length }}=\\frac{x}{0.2}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n$x$ is the displacement for second block.\nFor same material, $\\frac{\\text { stress }_1}{\\text { strain }_1}=\\frac{\\text { stress }_2}{\\text { strain }_2}$\n$$\n\\text { or, } \\frac{\\frac{10.5}{(0.1)^2}}{\\frac{0.5 \\times 10^{-2}}{0.1}}=\\frac{\\frac{10^5}{(0.2)^2}}{\\frac{x}{0.2}}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\text { Solving we get, } x=0.25 \\mathrm{~cm}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)","image":null}]